        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:25PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Toccoa, or near Avalon, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Martin, Avalon, and Eastanolee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
